The paper deals with the approximability of the Node-Disjoint Paths problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The problem is closely related to graph algorithms, computational complexity, and discrete mathematics, which are all covered by the arXiv categories of cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CG, and cs.DM. The paper also involves hardness of approximation, which is a topic in computational complexity theory and graph theory, and is covered by the arXiv category of cs.GT.
